{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"34":"Clothing (Kitab Al-Libas)"},"section_detail":{"34":{"hadithnumber_first":4020,"hadithnumber_last":4158,"arabicnumber_first":4020,"arabicnumber_last":4158}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":4058,"arabicnumber":4058,"text":"Anas ibn Malik رضي الله عنه a dit qu’il a vu un vêtement rayé sur Umm Kulthum, la fille du Messager d’Allah ﷺ. Il a précisé : Le mot « siyara » signifie rayé avec de la soie","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Hasan Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":34,"hadith":39}}]}